content:
Here is the cleaned up text:

Add milestones to entitlement processes to define required steps in your support process.

To add milestones to entitlement processes: 
- Manage Entitlements user permission
- From Setup, enter Entitlement Processes and click on a process
- Click New on the Milestones related list
- Choose the milestone
- In Time Trigger (Minutes), enter the number of minutes in which users must complete the milestone before it triggers an action

Choose when the milestone starts:
- Milestone Criteria: Calculate the milestone Target Date when the milestone is applied to a support record (matches the record criteria)
- Entitlement Process: Calculate the milestone Target Date when the entitlement process starts
- Optionally, select business hours for the Target Date calculation

Specify the order in which Salesforce should process the milestones.

Enter the criteria a record must match for the milestone to apply to it:
- Choose criteria are met and select filter criteria that a record must meet
- Choose formula evaluates to true and enter a formula that returns a value of “True” or “False”

Click Save.

Milestones are measured in minutes and seconds, but their start and end times are only accurate to the minute.
title: Adding Milestones to Entitlement Processes in Service Cloud
